{% extends 'layouts/page.njk' %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      
      <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Privacy notice</h1>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">The AI Content Review service is provided by the Department for Environment, Food & Rural Affairs (Defra).</p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">Defra is the data controller for this service. A data controller determines how and why personal data is processed.</p>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What data we collect</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">The personal data we collect from you includes:</p>

      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>your name and Defra email address, collected automatically when you sign in using your Defra Microsoft account (Azure Active Directory)</li>
        <li>sign-in events and session activity, recorded in our service logs</li>
        <li>content you submit to the service for AI review (text, URLs or uploaded documents)</li>
        <li>your Internet Protocol (IP) address, and details of which version of web browser you used</li>
        <li>questions, queries or feedback you leave, including your email address if you contact us</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Why we need your data</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">We collect your personal data in order to:</p>
      
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>provide the AI content review service</li>
        <li>respond to any feedback you send us, if you've asked us to</li>
        <li>monitor use of the service to identify security threats</li>
        <li>monitor the performance of the service to identify inefficiencies and errors</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Our legal basis for processing your data</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">The legal basis for processing personal data in relation to service security is our legitimate interests, and the legitimate interests of our users, in ensuring the security and integrity of the AI Content Review service.</p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">The legal basis for processing all other personal data is that it's necessary:</p>
      
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>to perform a task in the public interest</li>
        <li>in the exercise of our functions as a government department</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What we do with your data</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">The data we collect may be shared with other government departments, agencies and organisations. It may also be shared with our technology suppliers, for example our hosting provider.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">We will share your data if we are required to do so by law — for example, by court order, or to prevent fraud or other crime.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">How your submitted content is processed</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">Content you submit for review is:</p>

      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>automatically scanned and any personally identifiable information (PII) is redacted before further processing</li>
        <li>sent to an AI language model for analysis, which returns suggestions to you based solely on predefined system prompt instructions</li>
        <li>stored in an AWS S3 bucket within the UK</li>
        <li><strong>not</strong> used to train, fine-tune or improve the AI model in any way</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="govuk-body">AI review suggestions are advisory only. They are generated purely from the content you submit and the service's predefined review criteria.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Service activity logs</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">Service activity, including sign-in events and usage data, is captured in OpenSearch dashboards. This information is used only for monitoring service performance, identifying errors and maintaining security.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">We will not:</p>

      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>sell or rent your data to third parties</li>
        <li>share your data with third parties for marketing purposes</li>
        <li>use your submitted content to train or improve any AI or machine learning model</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How long we keep your data</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">We will only retain your personal data for as long as it is needed for the purposes set out in this document or for as long as the law requires us to.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Review results and uploaded content</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">Review results and any uploaded content are automatically deleted from our active systems after <strong>5 days</strong>. We are working to establish a long-term archival process for older records in line with government records management policies. Until that is in place, data is not retained beyond the 5-day active period.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Service activity logs</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">Service activity logs, including sign-in events and usage data stored in OpenSearch, are retained in accordance with our infrastructure retention policies. Your IP address is included in these logs for security and monitoring purposes.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Cookies and sessions</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">Session cookies expire after 1 hour of inactivity, or immediately when you sign out. Cookie preference cookies are stored for 90 days.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Feedback</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">If you contact us using our feedback form, your message is submitted to an external Microsoft Forms service. Any personal data you include in your feedback is handled in accordance with <a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-gb/privacystatement" class="govuk-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Microsoft's privacy statement (opens in new tab)</a>. We do not store feedback submissions directly within this service.</p>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Where your data is processed and stored</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">We design, build and run our systems to make sure that your data is as safe as possible at all stages, both while it's processed and when it's stored.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">All personal data is stored within the UK. Content submitted for review is stored in an AWS S3 bucket. Service activity logs are stored in OpenSearch, both hosted within the UK.</p>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How we protect your data and keep it secure</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">We are committed to doing all that we can to keep your data secure. We have set up systems and processes to prevent unauthorised access or disclosure of your data — for example, we protect your data using varying levels of encryption.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">Access to this service is restricted to Defra staff authenticated via their Defra Microsoft account (Azure Active Directory). Users outside the Defra AAD tenant cannot sign in or access this service.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">Any personally identifiable information (PII) detected in content you submit is automatically redacted before the content is sent to the AI model for processing.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">We also make sure that any third parties that we deal with keep all personal data they process on our behalf secure.</p>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Your rights</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">You have the right to request:</p>
      
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>information about how your personal data is processed</li>
        <li>a copy of that personal data</li>
        <li>that anything inaccurate in your personal data is corrected immediately</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">You can also:</p>
      
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>raise an objection about how your personal data is processed</li>
        <li>request that your personal data is erased if there is no longer a justification for it</li>
        <li>ask that the processing of your personal data is restricted in certain circumstances</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">If you have any of these requests, contact Defra's Data Protection Manager.</p>
      
      <div class="govuk-inset-text">
        Data Protection Manager<br>
        Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs<br>
        Seacole Building<br>
        2 Marsham Street<br>
        London<br>
        SW1P 4DF<br>
        <br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:data.protection@defra.gov.uk" class="govuk-link">data.protection@defra.gov.uk</a>
      </div>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Cookies</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">Cookies are small files saved on your phone, tablet or computer when you visit a website.</p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">We use cookies only to make this service work. We do not use analytics or tracking cookies.</p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">Find out more about <a href="/cookies" class="govuk-link">the cookies we use</a>.</p>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Contact us or make a complaint</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">If you have feedback about this service or questions about how we use your data, you can <a href="https://forms.office.com/e/yA5mQ2kEb3?origin=lprLink" class="govuk-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">contact us using our feedback form (opens in new tab)</a>.</p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">Contact Defra's Data Protection Manager if you:</p>
      
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>have a question about anything in this privacy notice</li>
        <li>think that your personal data has been misused or mishandled</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">You can also make a complaint to the Information Commissioner, who is an independent regulator.</p>
      
      <div class="govuk-inset-text">
        Information Commissioner<br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:icocasework@ico.org.uk" class="govuk-link">icocasework@ico.org.uk</a><br>
        Telephone: 0303 123 1113<br>
        Monday to Friday, 9am to 4:30pm<br>
        <a href="https://www.gov.uk/call-charges" class="govuk-link">Find out about call charges</a><br>
        <br>
        Information Commissioner's Office<br>
        Wycliffe House<br>
        Water Lane<br>
        Wilmslow<br>
        Cheshire<br>
        SK9 5AF
      </div>
      
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Changes to this policy</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">We may change this privacy policy. In that case, the 'last updated' date at the bottom of this page will also change. Any changes to this privacy policy will apply to you and your data immediately.</p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">If these changes affect how your personal data is processed, Defra will take reasonable steps to let you know.</p>
      
      <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-top-8"><strong>Last updated:</strong> 27 April 2026</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
